      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal principle that has been instrumental in expanding civil rights and individual liberties in the United States. It ensures that the government cannot infringe upon fundamental rights, such as freedom of speech, privacy, and equality, without a compelling reason. This principle has been used to dismantle discriminatory laws and practices, such as segregation and unequal voting rights, thus promoting a more just and equitable society. By protecting these essential rights, substantive due process has played a vital role in shaping a more inclusive and democratic nation.",
